43ALWAYS_INLINE static void appendCodePoint(Vector<UChar>& destination, UChar32 codePoint)
44{
45 if (U_IS_BMP(codePoint)) {
46 destination.append(static_cast<UChar>(codePoint));
47 return;
48 }
49 destination.reserveCapacity(destination.size() + 2);
50 destination.uncheckedAppend(U16_LEAD(codePoint));
51 destination.uncheckedAppend(U16_TRAIL(codePoint));
52}

322template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isC0Control(CharacterType character) { return character <= 0x1F; }
323template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isC0ControlOrSpace(CharacterType character) { return character <= 0x20; }
324template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isTabOrNewline(CharacterType character) { return character <= 0xD && character >= 0x9 && character != 0xB && character != 0xC; }
325template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isInSimpleEncodeSet(CharacterType character) { return character > 0x7E || isC0Control(character); }
326template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isInFragmentEncodeSet(CharacterType character) { return character > 0x7E || character == '`' || ((characterClassTable[character] & QueryPercent) && character != '#'); }
327template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isInDefaultEncodeSet(CharacterType character) { return character > 0x7E || characterClassTable[character] & Default; }
328template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isInUserInfoEncodeSet(CharacterType character) { return character > 0x7E || characterClassTable[character] & UserInfo; }
329template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isPercentOrNonASCII(CharacterType character) { return !isASCII(character) || character == '%'; }
330template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isSlashQuestionOrHash(CharacterType character) { return character <= '\\' && characterClassTable[character] & SlashQuestionOrHash; }
331template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isValidSchemeCharacter(CharacterType character) { return character <= 'z' && characterClassTable[character] & ValidScheme; }
332template<typename CharacterType> ALWAYS_INLINE static bool isForbiddenHostCodePoint(CharacterType character) { return character <= '|' && characterClassTable[character] & ForbiddenHost; }
333ALWAYS_INLINE static bool shouldPercentEncodeQueryByte(uint8_t byte, const bool& urlIsSpecial)
334{
335 if (characterClassTable[byte] & QueryPercent)
336 return true;
337 if (byte == '\'' && urlIsSpecial)
338 return true;
339 return false;
340}

342bool URLParser::isInUserInfoEncodeSet(UChar c)
343{
344 return WTF::isInUserInfoEncodeSet(c);
345}

347template<typename CharacterType, URLParser::ReportSyntaxViolation reportSyntaxViolation>
348ALWAYS_INLINE void URLParser::advance(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator, const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition)
349{
350 ++iterator;
351 while (UNLIKELY(!iterator.atEnd() && isTabOrNewline(*iterator))) {
352 if (reportSyntaxViolation == ReportSyntaxViolation::Yes)
353 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
354 ++iterator;
355 }
356}
357
358template<typename CharacterType>
359bool URLParser::takesTwoAdvancesUntilEnd(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
360{
361 if (iterator.atEnd())
362 return false;
363 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
364 if (iterator.atEnd())
365 return false;
366 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
367 return iterator.atEnd();
368}

370template<typename CharacterType>
371ALWAYS_INLINE bool URLParser::isWindowsDriveLetter(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
372{
373 // https://url.spec.whatwg.org/#start-with-a-windows-drive-letter
374 if (iterator.atEnd() || !isASCIIAlpha(*iterator))
375 return false;
376 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
377 if (iterator.atEnd())
378 return false;
379 if (*iterator != ':' && *iterator != '|')
380 return false;
381 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
382 return iterator.atEnd() || *iterator == '/' || *iterator == '\\' || *iterator == '?' || *iterator == '#';
383}

385ALWAYS_INLINE void URLParser::appendToASCIIBuffer(UChar32 codePoint)
386{
387 ASSERT(isASCII(codePoint));
388 if (UNLIKELY(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation))
389 m_asciiBuffer.append(codePoint);
390}
391
392ALWAYS_INLINE void URLParser::appendToASCIIBuffer(const char* characters, size_t length)
393{
394 if (UNLIKELY(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation))
395 m_asciiBuffer.append(characters, length);
396}
397
398template<typename CharacterType>
399void URLParser::appendWindowsDriveLetter(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
400{
401 auto lengthWithOnlyOneSlashInPath = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1;
402 if (m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash > lengthWithOnlyOneSlashInPath) {
403 syntaxViolation(iterator);
404 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = lengthWithOnlyOneSlashInPath;
405 m_asciiBuffer.resize(lengthWithOnlyOneSlashInPath);
406 }
407 ASSERT(isWindowsDriveLetter(iterator));
408 appendToASCIIBuffer(*iterator);
409 advance(iterator);
410 ASSERT(!iterator.atEnd());
411 ASSERT(*iterator == ':' || *iterator == '|');
412 if (*iterator == '|')
413 syntaxViolation(iterator);
414 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
415 advance(iterator);
416}
417
418bool URLParser::copyBaseWindowsDriveLetter(const URL& base)
419{
420 if (base.protocolIs("file")) {
421 RELEASE_ASSERT(base.m_hostEnd + base.m_portLength < base.m_string.length());
422 if (base.m_string.is8Bit()) {
423 const LChar* begin = base.m_string.characters8();
424 CodePointIterator<LChar> c(begin + base.m_hostEnd + base.m_portLength + 1, begin + base.m_string.length());
425 if (isWindowsDriveLetter(c)) {
426 appendWindowsDriveLetter(c);
427 return true;
428 }
429 } else {
430 const UChar* begin = base.m_string.characters16();
431 CodePointIterator<UChar> c(begin + base.m_hostEnd + base.m_portLength + 1, begin + base.m_string.length());
432 if (isWindowsDriveLetter(c)) {
433 appendWindowsDriveLetter(c);
434 return true;
435 }
436 }
437 }
438 return false;
439}

441template<typename CharacterType>
442bool URLParser::shouldCopyFileURL(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
443{
444 if (!isWindowsDriveLetter(iterator))
445 return true;
446 if (iterator.atEnd())
447 return false;
448 advance(iterator);
449 if (iterator.atEnd())
450 return true;
451 advance(iterator);
452 if (iterator.atEnd())
453 return true;
454 return !isSlashQuestionOrHash(*iterator);
455}

457static void percentEncodeByte(uint8_t byte, Vector<LChar>& buffer)
458{
459 buffer.append('%');
460 buffer.append(upperNibbleToASCIIHexDigit(byte));
461 buffer.append(lowerNibbleToASCIIHexDigit(byte));
462}
463
464void URLParser::percentEncodeByte(uint8_t byte)
465{
466 ASSERT(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation);
467 appendToASCIIBuffer('%');
468 appendToASCIIBuffer(upperNibbleToASCIIHexDigit(byte));
469 appendToASCIIBuffer(lowerNibbleToASCIIHexDigit(byte));
470}
471
472const char replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncoded[10] = "%EF%BF%BD";
473const size_t replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncodedLength = sizeof(replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncoded) - 1;
474
475template<bool(*isInCodeSet)(UChar32), typename CharacterType>
476ALWAYS_INLINE void URLParser::utf8PercentEncode(const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
477{
478 ASSERT(!iterator.atEnd());
479 UChar32 codePoint = *iterator;
480 if (LIKELY(isASCII(codePoint))) {
481 if (UNLIKELY(isInCodeSet(codePoint))) {
482 syntaxViolation(iterator);
483 percentEncodeByte(codePoint);
484 } else
485 appendToASCIIBuffer(codePoint);
486 return;
487 }
488 ASSERT_WITH_MESSAGE(isInCodeSet(codePoint), "isInCodeSet should always return true for non-ASCII characters");
489 syntaxViolation(iterator);
490
491 uint8_t buffer[U8_MAX_LENGTH];
492 int32_t offset = 0;
493 UBool isError = false;
494 U8_APPEND(buffer, offset, U8_MAX_LENGTH, codePoint, isError);
495 if (isError) {
496 appendToASCIIBuffer(replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncoded, replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncodedLength);
497 return;
498 }
499 for (int32_t i = 0; i < offset; ++i)
500 percentEncodeByte(buffer[i]);
501}
502
503template<typename CharacterType>
504ALWAYS_INLINE void URLParser::utf8QueryEncode(const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
505{
506 ASSERT(!iterator.atEnd());
507 UChar32 codePoint = *iterator;
508 if (LIKELY(isASCII(codePoint))) {
509 if (UNLIKELY(shouldPercentEncodeQueryByte(codePoint, m_urlIsSpecial))) {
510 syntaxViolation(iterator);
511 percentEncodeByte(codePoint);
512 } else
513 appendToASCIIBuffer(codePoint);
514 return;
515 }
516
517 syntaxViolation(iterator);
518
519 uint8_t buffer[U8_MAX_LENGTH];
520 int32_t offset = 0;
521 UBool isError = false;
522 U8_APPEND(buffer, offset, U8_MAX_LENGTH, codePoint, isError);
523 if (isError) {
524 appendToASCIIBuffer(replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncoded, replacementCharacterUTF8PercentEncodedLength);
525 return;
526 }
527 for (int32_t i = 0; i < offset; ++i) {
528 auto byte = buffer[i];
529 if (shouldPercentEncodeQueryByte(byte, m_urlIsSpecial))
530 percentEncodeByte(byte);
531 else
532 appendToASCIIBuffer(byte);
533 }
534}

536template<typename CharacterType>
537void URLParser::encodeNonUTF8Query(const Vector<UChar>& source, const URLTextEncoding& encoding, CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
538{
539 auto encoded = encoding.encodeForURLParsing(StringView(source.data(), source.size()));
540 auto* data = encoded.data();
541 size_t length = encoded.size();
542
543 if (!length == !iterator.atEnd()) {
544 syntaxViolation(iterator);
545 return;
546 }
547
548 size_t i = 0;
549 for (; i < length; ++i) {
550 ASSERT(!iterator.atEnd());
551 uint8_t byte = data[i];
552 if (UNLIKELY(byte != *iterator)) {
553 syntaxViolation(iterator);
554 break;
555 }
556 if (UNLIKELY(shouldPercentEncodeQueryByte(byte, m_urlIsSpecial))) {
557 syntaxViolation(iterator);
558 break;
559 }
560 appendToASCIIBuffer(byte);
561 ++iterator;
562 }
563 while (!iterator.atEnd() && isTabOrNewline(*iterator))
564 ++iterator;
565 ASSERT((i == length) == iterator.atEnd());
566 for (; i < length; ++i) {
567 ASSERT(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation);
568 uint8_t byte = data[i];
569 if (shouldPercentEncodeQueryByte(byte, m_urlIsSpecial))
570 percentEncodeByte(byte);
571 else
572 appendToASCIIBuffer(byte);
573 }
574}

576std::optional<uint16_t> URLParser::defaultPortForProtocol(StringView scheme)
577{
578 static constexpr uint16_t ftpPort = 21;
579 static constexpr uint16_t httpPort = 80;
580 static constexpr uint16_t httpsPort = 443;
581 static constexpr uint16_t wsPort = 80;
582 static constexpr uint16_t wssPort = 443;
583
584 auto length = scheme.length();
585 if (!length)
586 return std::nullopt;
587 switch (scheme[0]) {
588 case 'w':
589 switch (length) {
590 case 2:
591 if (scheme[1] == 's')
592 return wsPort;
593 return std::nullopt;
594 case 3:
595 if (scheme[1] == 's'
596 && scheme[2] == 's')
597 return wssPort;
598 return std::nullopt;
599 default:
600 return false;
601 }
602 case 'h':
603 switch (length) {
604 case 4:
605 if (scheme[1] == 't'
606 && scheme[2] == 't'
607 && scheme[3] == 'p')
608 return httpPort;
609 return std::nullopt;
610 case 5:
611 if (scheme[1] == 't'
612 && scheme[2] == 't'
613 && scheme[3] == 'p'
614 && scheme[4] == 's')
615 return httpsPort;
616 return std::nullopt;
617 default:
618 return std::nullopt;
619 }
620 case 'f':
621 if (length == 3
622 && scheme[1] == 't'
623 && scheme[2] == 'p')
624 return ftpPort;
625 return std::nullopt;
626 default:
627 return std::nullopt;
628 }
629}
630
631enum class Scheme {
632 WS,
633 WSS,
634 File,
635 FTP,
636 HTTP,
637 HTTPS,
638 NonSpecial
639};
640
641ALWAYS_INLINE static Scheme scheme(StringView scheme)
642{
643 auto length = scheme.length();
644 if (!length)
645 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
646 switch (scheme[0]) {
647 case 'f':
648 switch (length) {
649 case 3:
650 if (scheme[1] == 't'
651 && scheme[2] == 'p')
652 return Scheme::FTP;
653 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
654 case 4:
655 if (scheme[1] == 'i'
656 && scheme[2] == 'l'
657 && scheme[3] == 'e')
658 return Scheme::File;
659 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
660 default:
661 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
662 }
663 case 'h':
664 switch (length) {
665 case 4:
666 if (scheme[1] == 't'
667 && scheme[2] == 't'
668 && scheme[3] == 'p')
669 return Scheme::HTTP;
670 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
671 case 5:
672 if (scheme[1] == 't'
673 && scheme[2] == 't'
674 && scheme[3] == 'p'
675 && scheme[4] == 's')
676 return Scheme::HTTPS;
677 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
678 default:
679 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
680 }
681 case 'w':
682 switch (length) {
683 case 2:
684 if (scheme[1] == 's')
685 return Scheme::WS;
686 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
687 case 3:
688 if (scheme[1] == 's'
689 && scheme[2] == 's')
690 return Scheme::WSS;
691 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
692 default:
693 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
694 }
695 default:
696 return Scheme::NonSpecial;
697 }
698}
699
700std::optional<String> URLParser::maybeCanonicalizeScheme(StringView scheme)
701{
702 if (scheme.isEmpty())
703 return std::nullopt;
704
705 if (!isASCIIAlpha(scheme[0]))
706 return std::nullopt;
707
708 for (size_t i = 1; i < scheme.length(); ++i) {
709 if (isASCIIAlphanumeric(scheme[i]) || scheme[i] == '+' || scheme[i] == '-' || scheme[i] == '.')
710 continue;
711 return std::nullopt;
712 }
713
714 return scheme.convertToASCIILowercase();
715}
716
717bool URLParser::isSpecialScheme(const String& schemeArg)
718{
719 return scheme(schemeArg) != Scheme::NonSpecial;
720}

722enum class URLParser::URLPart {
723 SchemeEnd,
724 UserStart,
725 UserEnd,
726 PasswordEnd,
727 HostEnd,
728 PortEnd,
729 PathAfterLastSlash,
730 PathEnd,
731 QueryEnd,
732};
733
734size_t URLParser::urlLengthUntilPart(const URL& url, URLPart part)
735{
736 switch (part) {
737 case URLPart::QueryEnd:
738 return url.m_queryEnd;
739 case URLPart::PathEnd:
740 return url.m_pathEnd;
741 case URLPart::PathAfterLastSlash:
742 return url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
743 case URLPart::PortEnd:
744 return url.m_hostEnd + url.m_portLength;
745 case URLPart::HostEnd:
746 return url.m_hostEnd;
747 case URLPart::PasswordEnd:
748 return url.m_passwordEnd;
749 case URLPart::UserEnd:
750 return url.m_userEnd;
751 case URLPart::UserStart:
752 return url.m_userStart;
753 case URLPart::SchemeEnd:
754 return url.m_schemeEnd;
755 }
756 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
757 return 0;
758}
759
760void URLParser::copyASCIIStringUntil(const String& string, size_t length)
761{
762 RELEASE_ASSERT(length <= string.length());
763 if (string.isNull())
764 return;
765 ASSERT(m_asciiBuffer.isEmpty());
766 if (string.is8Bit())
767 appendToASCIIBuffer(string.characters8(), length);
768 else {
769 const UChar* characters = string.characters16();
770 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
771 UChar c = characters[i];
772 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(isASCII(c));
773 appendToASCIIBuffer(c);
774 }
775 }
776}
777
778template<typename CharacterType>
779void URLParser::copyURLPartsUntil(const URL& base, URLPart part, const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator, const URLTextEncoding*& nonUTF8QueryEncoding)
780{
781 syntaxViolation(iterator);
782
783 m_asciiBuffer.clear();
784 copyASCIIStringUntil(base.m_string, urlLengthUntilPart(base, part));
785 switch (part) {
786 case URLPart::QueryEnd:
787 m_url.m_queryEnd = base.m_queryEnd;
788 FALLTHROUGH;
789 case URLPart::PathEnd:
790 m_url.m_pathEnd = base.m_pathEnd;
791 FALLTHROUGH;
792 case URLPart::PathAfterLastSlash:
793 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = base.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
794 FALLTHROUGH;
795 case URLPart::PortEnd:
796 m_url.m_portLength = base.m_portLength;
797 FALLTHROUGH;
798 case URLPart::HostEnd:
799 m_url.m_hostEnd = base.m_hostEnd;
800 FALLTHROUGH;
801 case URLPart::PasswordEnd:
802 m_url.m_passwordEnd = base.m_passwordEnd;
803 FALLTHROUGH;
804 case URLPart::UserEnd:
805 m_url.m_userEnd = base.m_userEnd;
806 FALLTHROUGH;
807 case URLPart::UserStart:
808 m_url.m_userStart = base.m_userStart;
809 FALLTHROUGH;
810 case URLPart::SchemeEnd:
811 m_url.m_isValid = base.m_isValid;
812 m_url.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily = base.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily;
813 m_url.m_schemeEnd = base.m_schemeEnd;
814 }
815
816 switch (scheme(StringView(m_asciiBuffer.data(), m_url.m_schemeEnd))) {
817 case Scheme::WS:
818 case Scheme::WSS:
819 nonUTF8QueryEncoding = nullptr;
820 m_urlIsSpecial = true;
821 return;
822 case Scheme::File:
823 m_urlIsFile = true;
824 FALLTHROUGH;
825 case Scheme::FTP:
826 case Scheme::HTTP:
827 case Scheme::HTTPS:
828 m_urlIsSpecial = true;
829 return;
830 case Scheme::NonSpecial:
831 m_urlIsSpecial = false;
832 nonUTF8QueryEncoding = nullptr;
833 auto pathStart = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength;
834 if (pathStart + 2 < m_asciiBuffer.size()
835 && m_asciiBuffer[pathStart] == '/'
836 && m_asciiBuffer[pathStart + 1] == '.'
837 && m_asciiBuffer[pathStart + 2] == '/') {
838 m_asciiBuffer.remove(pathStart + 1, 2);
839 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = std::max(2u, m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash) - 2;
840 m_url.m_pathEnd = std::max(2u, m_url.m_pathEnd) - 2;
841 m_url.m_queryEnd = std::max(2u, m_url.m_queryEnd) - 2;
842 }
843 return;
844 }
845 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
846}
847
848static const char dotASCIICode[2] = {'2', 'e'};
849
850template<typename CharacterType>
851ALWAYS_INLINE bool URLParser::isSingleDotPathSegment(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> c)
852{
853 if (c.atEnd())
854 return false;
855 if (*c == '.') {
856 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
857 return c.atEnd() || isSlashQuestionOrHash(*c);
858 }
859 if (*c != '%')
860 return false;
861 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
862 if (c.atEnd() || *c != dotASCIICode[0])
863 return false;
864 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
865 if (c.atEnd())
866 return false;
867 if (toASCIILower(*c) == dotASCIICode[1]) {
868 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
869 return c.atEnd() || isSlashQuestionOrHash(*c);
870 }
871 return false;
872}
873
874template<typename CharacterType>
875ALWAYS_INLINE bool URLParser::isDoubleDotPathSegment(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> c)
876{
877 if (c.atEnd())
878 return false;
879 if (*c == '.') {
880 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
881 return isSingleDotPathSegment(c);
882 }
883 if (*c != '%')
884 return false;
885 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
886 if (c.atEnd() || *c != dotASCIICode[0])
887 return false;
888 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
889 if (c.atEnd())
890 return false;
891 if (toASCIILower(*c) == dotASCIICode[1]) {
892 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(c);
893 return isSingleDotPathSegment(c);
894 }
895 return false;
896}
897
898template<typename CharacterType>
899void URLParser::consumeSingleDotPathSegment(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& c)
900{
901 ASSERT(isSingleDotPathSegment(c));
902 if (*c == '.') {
903 advance(c);
904 if (!c.atEnd()) {
905 if (*c == '/' || *c == '\\')
906 advance(c);
907 else
908 ASSERT(*c == '?' || *c == '#');
909 }
910 } else {
911 ASSERT(*c == '%');
912 advance(c);
913 ASSERT(*c == dotASCIICode[0]);
914 advance(c);
915 ASSERT(toASCIILower(*c) == dotASCIICode[1]);
916 advance(c);
917 if (!c.atEnd()) {
918 if (*c == '/' || *c == '\\')
919 advance(c);
920 else
921 ASSERT(*c == '?' || *c == '#');
922 }
923 }
924}
925
926template<typename CharacterType>
927void URLParser::consumeDoubleDotPathSegment(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& c)
928{
929 ASSERT(isDoubleDotPathSegment(c));
930 if (*c == '.')
931 advance(c);
932 else {
933 ASSERT(*c == '%');
934 advance(c);
935 ASSERT(*c == dotASCIICode[0]);
936 advance(c);
937 ASSERT(toASCIILower(*c) == dotASCIICode[1]);
938 advance(c);
939 }
940 consumeSingleDotPathSegment(c);
941}
942
943bool URLParser::shouldPopPath(unsigned newPathAfterLastSlash)
944{
945 ASSERT(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation);
946 if (!m_urlIsFile)
947 return true;
948
949 ASSERT(m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash <= m_asciiBuffer.size());
950 CodePointIterator<LChar> componentToPop(&m_asciiBuffer[newPathAfterLastSlash], &m_asciiBuffer[0] + m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash);
951 if (newPathAfterLastSlash == m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1 && isWindowsDriveLetter(componentToPop))
952 return false;
953 return true;
954}
955
956void URLParser::popPath()
957{
958 ASSERT(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation);
959 if (m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash > m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1) {
960 auto newPathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash - 1;
961 if (m_asciiBuffer[newPathAfterLastSlash] == '/')
962 newPathAfterLastSlash--;
963 while (newPathAfterLastSlash > m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength && m_asciiBuffer[newPathAfterLastSlash] != '/')
964 newPathAfterLastSlash--;
965 newPathAfterLastSlash++;
966 if (shouldPopPath(newPathAfterLastSlash))
967 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = newPathAfterLastSlash;
968 }
969 m_asciiBuffer.resize(m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash);
970}
971
972template<typename CharacterType>
973void URLParser::syntaxViolation(const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
974{
975 if (m_didSeeSyntaxViolation)
976 return;
977 m_didSeeSyntaxViolation = true;
978
979 ASSERT(m_asciiBuffer.isEmpty());
980 size_t codeUnitsToCopy = iterator.codeUnitsSince(reinterpret_cast<const CharacterType*>(m_inputBegin));
981 RELEASE_ASSERT(codeUnitsToCopy <= m_inputString.length());
982 m_asciiBuffer.reserveCapacity(m_inputString.length());
983 for (size_t i = 0; i < codeUnitsToCopy; ++i) {
984 ASSERT(isASCII(m_inputString[i]));
985 m_asciiBuffer.uncheckedAppend(m_inputString[i]);
986 }
987}
988
989void URLParser::failure()
990{
991 m_url.invalidate();
992 m_url.m_string = m_inputString;
993}
994
995template<typename CharacterType>
996bool URLParser::checkLocalhostCodePoint(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator, UChar32 codePoint)
997{
998 if (iterator.atEnd() || toASCIILower(*iterator) != codePoint)
999 return false;
1000 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
1001 return true;
1002}
1003
1004template<typename CharacterType>
1005bool URLParser::isAtLocalhost(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
1006{
1007 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'l'))
1008 return false;
1009 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'o'))
1010 return false;
1011 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'c'))
1012 return false;
1013 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'a'))
1014 return false;
1015 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'l'))
1016 return false;
1017 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'h'))
1018 return false;
1019 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 'o'))
1020 return false;
1021 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 's'))
1022 return false;
1023 if (!checkLocalhostCodePoint(iterator, 't'))
1024 return false;
1025 return iterator.atEnd();
1026}
1027
1028bool URLParser::isLocalhost(StringView view)
1029{
1030 if (view.is8Bit())
1031 return isAtLocalhost(CodePointIterator<LChar>(view.characters8(), view.characters8() + view.length()));
1032 return isAtLocalhost(CodePointIterator<UChar>(view.characters16(), view.characters16() + view.length()));
1033}
1034
1035ALWAYS_INLINE StringView URLParser::parsedDataView(size_t start, size_t length)
1036{
1037 if (UNLIKELY(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation)) {
1038 ASSERT(start + length <= m_asciiBuffer.size());
1039 return StringView(m_asciiBuffer.data() + start, length);
1040 }
1041 ASSERT(start + length <= m_inputString.length());
1042 return StringView(m_inputString).substring(start, length);
1043}
1044
1045ALWAYS_INLINE UChar URLParser::parsedDataView(size_t position)
1046{
1047 if (UNLIKELY(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation))
1048 return m_asciiBuffer[position];
1049 return m_inputString[position];
1050}
1051
1052template<typename CharacterType>
1053ALWAYS_INLINE size_t URLParser::currentPosition(const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
1054{
1055 if (UNLIKELY(m_didSeeSyntaxViolation))
1056 return m_asciiBuffer.size();
1057
1058 return iterator.codeUnitsSince(reinterpret_cast<const CharacterType*>(m_inputBegin));
1059}
1060
1061URLParser::URLParser(const String& input, const URL& base, const URLTextEncoding* nonUTF8QueryEncoding)
1062 : m_inputString(input)
1063{
1064 if (input.isNull()) {
1065 if (base.isValid() && !base.m_cannotBeABaseURL) {
1066 m_url = base;
1067 m_url.removeFragmentIdentifier();
1068 }
1069 return;
1070 }
1071
1072 if (input.is8Bit()) {
1073 m_inputBegin = input.characters8();
1074 parse(input.characters8(), input.length(), base, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1075 } else {
1076 m_inputBegin = input.characters16();
1077 parse(input.characters16(), input.length(), base, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1078 }
1079
1080 ASSERT(!m_url.m_isValid
1081 || m_didSeeSyntaxViolation == (m_url.string() != input)
1082 || (input.isAllSpecialCharacters<isC0ControlOrSpace>() && m_url.m_string == base.m_string.left(base.m_queryEnd))
1083 || (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")));
1084 ASSERT(internalValuesConsistent(m_url));
1085#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1086 if (!m_didSeeSyntaxViolation) {
1087 // Force a syntax violation at the beginning to make sure we get the same result.
1088 URLParser parser(makeString(" ", input), base, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1089 URL parsed = parser.result();
1090 if (parsed.isValid())
1091 ASSERT(allValuesEqual(parser.result(), m_url));
1092 }
1093#endif // ASSERT_ENABLED
1094
1095 if (UNLIKELY(needsNonSpecialDotSlash()))
1096 addNonSpecialDotSlash();
1097}
1098
1099template<typename CharacterType>
1100void URLParser::parse(const CharacterType* input, const unsigned length, const URL& base, const URLTextEncoding* nonUTF8QueryEncoding)
1101{
1102 URL_PARSER_LOG("Parsing URL <%s> base <%s>", String(input, length).utf8().data(), base.string().utf8().data());
1103 m_url = { };
1104 ASSERT(m_asciiBuffer.isEmpty());
1105
1106 Vector<UChar> queryBuffer;
1107
1108 unsigned endIndex = length;
1109 while (UNLIKELY(endIndex && isC0ControlOrSpace(input[endIndex - 1]))) {
1110 syntaxViolation(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(input, input));
1111 endIndex--;
1112 }
1113 CodePointIterator<CharacterType> c(input, input + endIndex);
1114 CodePointIterator<CharacterType> authorityOrHostBegin;
1115 CodePointIterator<CharacterType> queryBegin;
1116 while (UNLIKELY(!c.atEnd() && isC0ControlOrSpace(*c))) {
1117 syntaxViolation(c);
1118 ++c;
1119 }
1120 auto beginAfterControlAndSpace = c;
1121
1122 enum class State : uint8_t {
1123 SchemeStart,
1124 Scheme,
1125 NoScheme,
1126 SpecialRelativeOrAuthority,
1127 PathOrAuthority,
1128 Relative,
1129 RelativeSlash,
1130 SpecialAuthoritySlashes,
1131 SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes,
1132 AuthorityOrHost,
1133 Host,
1134 File,
1135 FileSlash,
1136 FileHost,
1137 PathStart,
1138 Path,
1139 CannotBeABaseURLPath,
1140 UTF8Query,
1141 NonUTF8Query,
1142 Fragment,
1143 };
1144
1145#define LOG_STATE(x) URL_PARSER_LOG("State %s, code point %c, parsed data <%s> size %zu", x, *c, parsedDataView(0, currentPosition(c)).utf8().data(), currentPosition(c))
1146#define LOG_FINAL_STATE(x) URL_PARSER_LOG("Final State: %s", x)
1147
1148 State state = State::SchemeStart;
1149 while (!c.atEnd()) {
1150 if (UNLIKELY(isTabOrNewline(*c))) {
1151 syntaxViolation(c);
1152 ++c;
1153 continue;
1154 }
1155
1156 switch (state) {
1157 case State::SchemeStart:
1158 LOG_STATE("SchemeStart");
1159 if (isASCIIAlpha(*c)) {
1160 if (UNLIKELY(isASCIIUpper(*c)))
1161 syntaxViolation(c);
1162 appendToASCIIBuffer(toASCIILower(*c));
1163 advance(c);
1164 if (c.atEnd()) {
1165 m_asciiBuffer.clear();
1166 state = State::NoScheme;
1167 c = beginAfterControlAndSpace;
1168 break;
1169 }
1170 state = State::Scheme;
1171 } else
1172 state = State::NoScheme;
1173 break;
1174 case State::Scheme:
1175 LOG_STATE("Scheme");
1176 if (isValidSchemeCharacter(*c)) {
1177 if (UNLIKELY(isASCIIUpper(*c)))
1178 syntaxViolation(c);
1179 appendToASCIIBuffer(toASCIILower(*c));
1180 } else if (*c == ':') {
1181 unsigned schemeEnd = currentPosition(c);
1182 if (schemeEnd > URL::maxSchemeLength) {
1183 failure();
1184 return;
1185 }
1186 m_url.m_schemeEnd = schemeEnd;
1187 StringView urlScheme = parsedDataView(0, m_url.m_schemeEnd);
1188 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
1189 switch (scheme(urlScheme)) {
1190 case Scheme::File:
1191 m_urlIsSpecial = true;
1192 m_urlIsFile = true;
1193 state = State::File;
1194 ++c;
1195 break;
1196 case Scheme::WS:
1197 case Scheme::WSS:
1198 nonUTF8QueryEncoding = nullptr;
1199 m_urlIsSpecial = true;
1200 if (base.protocolIs(urlScheme))
1201 state = State::SpecialRelativeOrAuthority;
1202 else
1203 state = State::SpecialAuthoritySlashes;
1204 ++c;
1205 break;
1206 case Scheme::HTTP:
1207 case Scheme::HTTPS:
1208 m_url.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily = true;
1209 FALLTHROUGH;
1210 case Scheme::FTP:
1211 m_urlIsSpecial = true;
1212 if (base.protocolIs(urlScheme))
1213 state = State::SpecialRelativeOrAuthority;
1214 else
1215 state = State::SpecialAuthoritySlashes;
1216 ++c;
1217 break;
1218 case Scheme::NonSpecial:
1219 nonUTF8QueryEncoding = nullptr;
1220 auto maybeSlash = c;
1221 advance(maybeSlash);
1222 if (!maybeSlash.atEnd() && *maybeSlash == '/') {
1223 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1224 c = maybeSlash;
1225 state = State::PathOrAuthority;
1226 ASSERT(*c == '/');
1227 ++c;
1228 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1229 } else {
1230 ++c;
1231 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1232 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1233 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1234 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1235 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1236 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart;
1237 m_url.m_cannotBeABaseURL = true;
1238 state = State::CannotBeABaseURLPath;
1239 }
1240 break;
1241 }
1242 break;
1243 } else {
1244 m_asciiBuffer.clear();
1245 state = State::NoScheme;
1246 c = beginAfterControlAndSpace;
1247 break;
1248 }
1249 advance(c);
1250 if (c.atEnd()) {
1251 m_asciiBuffer.clear();
1252 state = State::NoScheme;
1253 c = beginAfterControlAndSpace;
1254 }
1255 break;
1256 case State::NoScheme:
1257 LOG_STATE("NoScheme");
1258 if (!base.isValid() || (base.m_cannotBeABaseURL && *c != '#')) {
1259 failure();
1260 return;
1261 }
1262 if (base.m_cannotBeABaseURL && *c == '#') {
1263 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::QueryEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1264 state = State::Fragment;
1265 appendToASCIIBuffer('#');
1266 ++c;
1267 break;
1268 }
1269 if (!base.protocolIs("file")) {
1270 state = State::Relative;
1271 break;
1272 }
1273 state = State::File;
1274 break;
1275 case State::SpecialRelativeOrAuthority:
1276 LOG_STATE("SpecialRelativeOrAuthority");
1277 if (*c == '/') {
1278 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1279 advance(c);
1280 if (c.atEnd()) {
1281 failure();
1282 return;
1283 }
1284 if (*c == '/') {
1285 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1286 state = State::SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes;
1287 ++c;
1288 } else
1289 state = State::RelativeSlash;
1290 } else
1291 state = State::Relative;
1292 break;
1293 case State::PathOrAuthority:
1294 LOG_STATE("PathOrAuthority");
1295 if (*c == '/') {
1296 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1297 state = State::AuthorityOrHost;
1298 advance(c);
1299 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1300 authorityOrHostBegin = c;
1301 } else {
1302 ASSERT(parsedDataView(currentPosition(c) - 1) == '/');
1303 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1304 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1305 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1306 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1307 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1308 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1309 state = State::Path;
1310 }
1311 break;
1312 case State::Relative:
1313 LOG_STATE("Relative");
1314 switch (*c) {
1315 case '/':
1316 case '\\':
1317 state = State::RelativeSlash;
1318 ++c;
1319 break;
1320 case '?':
1321 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PathEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1322 appendToASCIIBuffer('?');
1323 ++c;
1324 if (nonUTF8QueryEncoding) {
1325 queryBegin = c;
1326 state = State::NonUTF8Query;
1327 } else
1328 state = State::UTF8Query;
1329 break;
1330 case '#':
1331 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::QueryEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1332 appendToASCIIBuffer('#');
1333 state = State::Fragment;
1334 ++c;
1335 break;
1336 default:
1337 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PathAfterLastSlash, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1338 if ((currentPosition(c) && parsedDataView(currentPosition(c) - 1) != '/')
1339 || (base.host().isEmpty() && base.path().isEmpty())) {
1340 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1341 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1342 }
1343 state = State::Path;
1344 break;
1345 }
1346 break;
1347 case State::RelativeSlash:
1348 LOG_STATE("RelativeSlash");
1349 if (*c == '/' || *c == '\\') {
1350 ++c;
1351 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::SchemeEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1352 appendToASCIIBuffer("://", 3);
1353 if (m_urlIsSpecial)
1354 state = State::SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes;
1355 else {
1356 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1357 state = State::AuthorityOrHost;
1358 authorityOrHostBegin = c;
1359 }
1360 } else {
1361 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PortEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1362 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1363 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = base.m_hostEnd + base.m_portLength + 1;
1364 state = State::Path;
1365 }
1366 break;
1367 case State::SpecialAuthoritySlashes:
1368 LOG_STATE("SpecialAuthoritySlashes");
1369 if (LIKELY(*c == '/' || *c == '\\')) {
1370 if (UNLIKELY(*c == '\\'))
1371 syntaxViolation(c);
1372 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1373 advance(c);
1374 if (LIKELY(!c.atEnd() && (*c == '/' || *c == '\\'))) {
1375 if (UNLIKELY(*c == '\\'))
1376 syntaxViolation(c);
1377 ++c;
1378 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1379 } else {
1380 syntaxViolation(c);
1381 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1382 }
1383 } else {
1384 syntaxViolation(c);
1385 appendToASCIIBuffer("//", 2);
1386 }
1387 state = State::SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes;
1388 break;
1389 case State::SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes:
1390 LOG_STATE("SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes");
1391 if (*c == '/' || *c == '\\') {
1392 syntaxViolation(c);
1393 ++c;
1394 } else {
1395 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1396 state = State::AuthorityOrHost;
1397 authorityOrHostBegin = c;
1398 }
1399 break;
1400 case State::AuthorityOrHost:
1401 do {
1402 LOG_STATE("AuthorityOrHost");
1403 if (*c == '@') {
1404 auto lastAt = c;
1405 auto findLastAt = c;
1406 while (!findLastAt.atEnd()) {
1407 URL_PARSER_LOG("Finding last @: %c", *findLastAt);
1408 if (*findLastAt == '@')
1409 lastAt = findLastAt;
1410 bool isSlash = *findLastAt == '/' || (m_urlIsSpecial && *findLastAt == '\\');
1411 if (isSlash || *findLastAt == '?' || *findLastAt == '#')
1412 break;
1413 ++findLastAt;
1414 }
1415 parseAuthority(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, lastAt));
1416 c = lastAt;
1417 advance(c);
1418 authorityOrHostBegin = c;
1419 state = State::Host;
1420 m_hostHasPercentOrNonASCII = false;
1421 break;
1422 }
1423 bool isSlash = *c == '/' || (m_urlIsSpecial && *c == '\\');
1424 if (isSlash || *c == '?' || *c == '#') {
1425 auto iterator = CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c);
1426 if (iterator.atEnd()) {
1427 if (m_urlIsSpecial)
1428 return failure();
1429 m_url.m_userEnd = currentPosition(c);
1430 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
1431 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
1432 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1433 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userEnd;
1434 } else {
1435 m_url.m_userEnd = currentPosition(authorityOrHostBegin);
1436 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
1437 if (!parseHostAndPort(iterator)) {
1438 failure();
1439 return;
1440 }
1441 if (UNLIKELY(!isSlash)) {
1442 if (m_urlIsSpecial) {
1443 syntaxViolation(c);
1444 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1445 }
1446 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1447 }
1448 }
1449 state = State::Path;
1450 break;
1451 }
1452 if (isPercentOrNonASCII(*c))
1453 m_hostHasPercentOrNonASCII = true;
1454 ++c;
1455 } while (!c.atEnd());
1456 break;
1457 case State::Host:
1458 do {
1459 LOG_STATE("Host");
1460 if (*c == '/' || *c == '?' || *c == '#') {
1461 if (!parseHostAndPort(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c))) {
1462 failure();
1463 return;
1464 }
1465 if (*c == '?' || *c == '#') {
1466 syntaxViolation(c);
1467 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1468 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1469 }
1470 state = State::Path;
1471 break;
1472 }
1473 if (isPercentOrNonASCII(*c))
1474 m_hostHasPercentOrNonASCII = true;
1475 ++c;
1476 } while (!c.atEnd());
1477 break;
1478 case State::File:
1479 LOG_STATE("File");
1480 switch (*c) {
1481 case '\\':
1482 syntaxViolation(c);
1483 FALLTHROUGH;
1484 case '/':
1485 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1486 state = State::FileSlash;
1487 ++c;
1488 break;
1489 case '?':
1490 syntaxViolation(c);
1491 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1492 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PathEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1493 appendToASCIIBuffer('?');
1494 ++c;
1495 } else {
1496 appendToASCIIBuffer("///?", 4);
1497 ++c;
1498 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 2;
1499 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1500 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1501 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1502 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1503 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1504 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1505 }
1506 if (nonUTF8QueryEncoding) {
1507 queryBegin = c;
1508 state = State::NonUTF8Query;
1509 } else
1510 state = State::UTF8Query;
1511 break;
1512 case '#':
1513 syntaxViolation(c);
1514 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1515 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::QueryEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1516 appendToASCIIBuffer('#');
1517 } else {
1518 appendToASCIIBuffer("///#", 4);
1519 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 2;
1520 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1521 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1522 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1523 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1524 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1525 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1526 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1527 }
1528 state = State::Fragment;
1529 ++c;
1530 break;
1531 default:
1532 syntaxViolation(c);
1533 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file") && shouldCopyFileURL(c))
1534 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PathAfterLastSlash, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1535 else {
1536 bool copiedHost = false;
1537 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1538 if (base.host().isEmpty()) {
1539 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::SchemeEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1540 appendToASCIIBuffer(":///", 4);
1541 } else {
1542 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PortEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1543 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1544 copiedHost = true;
1545 }
1546 } else
1547 appendToASCIIBuffer("///", 3);
1548 if (!copiedHost) {
1549 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1550 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1551 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1552 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1553 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1554 }
1555 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 1;
1556 }
1557 if (isWindowsDriveLetter(c))
1558 appendWindowsDriveLetter(c);
1559 state = State::Path;
1560 break;
1561 }
1562 break;
1563 case State::FileSlash:
1564 LOG_STATE("FileSlash");
1565 if (LIKELY(*c == '/' || *c == '\\')) {
1566 if (UNLIKELY(*c == '\\'))
1567 syntaxViolation(c);
1568 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1569 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::SchemeEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1570 appendToASCIIBuffer(":/", 2);
1571 }
1572 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1573 advance(c);
1574 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c);
1575 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1576 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1577 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1578 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1579 authorityOrHostBegin = c;
1580 state = State::FileHost;
1581 break;
1582 }
1583 {
1584 bool copiedHost = false;
1585 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1586 if (base.host().isEmpty()) {
1587 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::SchemeEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1588 appendToASCIIBuffer(":///", 4);
1589 } else {
1590 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PortEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1591 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1592 copiedHost = true;
1593 }
1594 } else {
1595 syntaxViolation(c);
1596 appendToASCIIBuffer("//", 2);
1597 }
1598 if (!copiedHost) {
1599 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1600 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1601 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1602 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1603 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1604 }
1605 }
1606 if (isWindowsDriveLetter(c)) {
1607 appendWindowsDriveLetter(c);
1608 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 1;
1609 } else if (copyBaseWindowsDriveLetter(base)) {
1610 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1611 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 4;
1612 } else
1613 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 1;
1614 state = State::Path;
1615 break;
1616 case State::FileHost:
1617 do {
1618 LOG_STATE("FileHost");
1619 if (isSlashQuestionOrHash(*c)) {
1620 bool windowsQuirk = takesTwoAdvancesUntilEnd(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c))
1621 && isWindowsDriveLetter(authorityOrHostBegin);
1622 if (windowsQuirk) {
1623 syntaxViolation(authorityOrHostBegin);
1624 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1625 appendWindowsDriveLetter(authorityOrHostBegin);
1626 }
1627 if (windowsQuirk || authorityOrHostBegin == c) {
1628 ASSERT(windowsQuirk || parsedDataView(currentPosition(c) - 1) == '/');
1629 if (UNLIKELY(*c == '?')) {
1630 syntaxViolation(c);
1631 appendToASCIIBuffer("/?", 2);
1632 ++c;
1633 if (nonUTF8QueryEncoding) {
1634 queryBegin = c;
1635 state = State::NonUTF8Query;
1636 } else
1637 state = State::UTF8Query;
1638 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1639 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1640 break;
1641 }
1642 if (UNLIKELY(*c == '#')) {
1643 syntaxViolation(c);
1644 appendToASCIIBuffer("/#", 2);
1645 ++c;
1646 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1647 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1648 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1649 state = State::Fragment;
1650 break;
1651 }
1652 state = State::Path;
1653 break;
1654 }
1655 if (!parseHostAndPort(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c))) {
1656 failure();
1657 return;
1658 }
1659 if (UNLIKELY(isLocalhost(parsedDataView(m_url.m_passwordEnd, currentPosition(c) - m_url.m_passwordEnd)))) {
1660 syntaxViolation(c);
1661 m_asciiBuffer.shrink(m_url.m_passwordEnd);
1662 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(c);
1663 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1664 }
1665
1666 state = State::PathStart;
1667 break;
1668 }
1669 if (isPercentOrNonASCII(*c))
1670 m_hostHasPercentOrNonASCII = true;
1671 ++c;
1672 } while (!c.atEnd());
1673 break;
1674 case State::PathStart:
1675 LOG_STATE("PathStart");
1676 if (*c != '/' && *c != '\\') {
1677 syntaxViolation(c);
1678 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1679 }
1680 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1681 state = State::Path;
1682 break;
1683 case State::Path:
1684 LOG_STATE("Path");
1685 if (*c == '/' || (m_urlIsSpecial && *c == '\\')) {
1686 if (UNLIKELY(m_urlIsSpecial && *c == '\\'))
1687 syntaxViolation(c);
1688 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1689 ++c;
1690 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1691 break;
1692 }
1693 if (UNLIKELY(currentPosition(c) && parsedDataView(currentPosition(c) - 1) == '/')) {
1694 if (UNLIKELY(isDoubleDotPathSegment(c))) {
1695 syntaxViolation(c);
1696 consumeDoubleDotPathSegment(c);
1697 popPath();
1698 break;
1699 }
1700 if (UNLIKELY(isSingleDotPathSegment(c))) {
1701 syntaxViolation(c);
1702 consumeSingleDotPathSegment(c);
1703 break;
1704 }
1705 }
1706 if (*c == '?') {
1707 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1708 appendToASCIIBuffer('?');
1709 ++c;
1710 if (nonUTF8QueryEncoding) {
1711 queryBegin = c;
1712 state = State::NonUTF8Query;
1713 } else
1714 state = State::UTF8Query;
1715 break;
1716 }
1717 if (*c == '#') {
1718 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1719 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1720 state = State::Fragment;
1721 break;
1722 }
1723 utf8PercentEncode<isInDefaultEncodeSet>(c);
1724 ++c;
1725 break;
1726 case State::CannotBeABaseURLPath:
1727 LOG_STATE("CannotBeABaseURLPath");
1728 if (*c == '?') {
1729 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1730 appendToASCIIBuffer('?');
1731 ++c;
1732 if (nonUTF8QueryEncoding) {
1733 queryBegin = c;
1734 state = State::NonUTF8Query;
1735 } else
1736 state = State::UTF8Query;
1737 } else if (*c == '#') {
1738 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1739 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1740 state = State::Fragment;
1741 } else if (*c == '/') {
1742 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1743 ++c;
1744 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1745 } else {
1746 utf8PercentEncode<isInSimpleEncodeSet>(c);
1747 ++c;
1748 }
1749 break;
1750 case State::UTF8Query:
1751 LOG_STATE("UTF8Query");
1752 ASSERT(queryBegin == CodePointIterator<CharacterType>());
1753 if (*c == '#') {
1754 m_url.m_queryEnd = currentPosition(c);
1755 state = State::Fragment;
1756 break;
1757 }
1758 ASSERT(!nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1759 utf8QueryEncode(c);
1760 ++c;
1761 break;
1762 case State::NonUTF8Query:
1763 do {
1764 LOG_STATE("NonUTF8Query");
1765 ASSERT(queryBegin != CodePointIterator<CharacterType>());
1766 if (*c == '#') {
1767 encodeNonUTF8Query(queryBuffer, *nonUTF8QueryEncoding, CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(queryBegin, c));
1768 m_url.m_queryEnd = currentPosition(c);
1769 state = State::Fragment;
1770 break;
1771 }
1772 appendCodePoint(queryBuffer, *c);
1773 advance(c, queryBegin);
1774 } while (!c.atEnd());
1775 break;
1776 case State::Fragment:
1777 URL_PARSER_LOG("State Fragment");
1778 utf8PercentEncode<isInFragmentEncodeSet>(c);
1779 ++c;
1780 break;
1781 }
1782 }
1783
1784 switch (state) {
1785 case State::SchemeStart:
1786 LOG_FINAL_STATE("SchemeStart");
1787 if (!currentPosition(c) && base.isValid() && !base.m_cannotBeABaseURL) {
1788 m_url = base;
1789 m_url.removeFragmentIdentifier();
1790 return;
1791 }
1792 failure();
1793 return;
1794 case State::Scheme:
1795 LOG_FINAL_STATE("Scheme");
1796 failure();
1797 return;
1798 case State::NoScheme:
1799 LOG_FINAL_STATE("NoScheme");
1800 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1801 case State::SpecialRelativeOrAuthority:
1802 LOG_FINAL_STATE("SpecialRelativeOrAuthority");
1803 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::QueryEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1804 break;
1805 case State::PathOrAuthority:
1806 LOG_FINAL_STATE("PathOrAuthority");
1807 ASSERT(m_url.m_userStart);
1808 ASSERT(m_url.m_userStart == currentPosition(c));
1809 ASSERT(parsedDataView(currentPosition(c) - 1) == '/');
1810 m_url.m_userStart--;
1811 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1812 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1813 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1814 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1815 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1816 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1817 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1818 break;
1819 case State::Relative:
1820 LOG_FINAL_STATE("Relative");
1821 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1822 case State::RelativeSlash:
1823 LOG_FINAL_STATE("RelativeSlash");
1824 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PortEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1825 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1826 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1;
1827 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1828 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1829 break;
1830 case State::SpecialAuthoritySlashes:
1831 LOG_FINAL_STATE("SpecialAuthoritySlashes");
1832 failure();
1833 return;
1834 case State::SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes:
1835 LOG_FINAL_STATE("SpecialAuthorityIgnoreSlashes");
1836 failure();
1837 return;
1838 case State::AuthorityOrHost:
1839 LOG_FINAL_STATE("AuthorityOrHost");
1840 m_url.m_userEnd = currentPosition(authorityOrHostBegin);
1841 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
1842 if (authorityOrHostBegin.atEnd()) {
1843 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1844 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1845 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1846 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1847 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1848 } else if (!parseHostAndPort(authorityOrHostBegin)) {
1849 failure();
1850 return;
1851 } else {
1852 if (m_urlIsSpecial) {
1853 syntaxViolation(c);
1854 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1855 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1;
1856 } else
1857 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength;
1858 }
1859 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1860 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1861 break;
1862 case State::Host:
1863 LOG_FINAL_STATE("Host");
1864 if (!parseHostAndPort(authorityOrHostBegin)) {
1865 failure();
1866 return;
1867 }
1868 if (m_urlIsSpecial) {
1869 syntaxViolation(c);
1870 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1871 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1;
1872 } else
1873 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength;
1874 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1875 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1876 break;
1877 case State::File:
1878 LOG_FINAL_STATE("File");
1879 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1880 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::QueryEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1881 break;
1882 }
1883 syntaxViolation(c);
1884 appendToASCIIBuffer("///", 3);
1885 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1886 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1887 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1888 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1889 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1890 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1891 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1892 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1893 break;
1894 case State::FileSlash:
1895 LOG_FINAL_STATE("FileSlash");
1896 syntaxViolation(c);
1897 {
1898 bool copiedHost = false;
1899 if (base.isValid() && base.protocolIs("file")) {
1900 if (base.host().isEmpty()) {
1901 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::SchemeEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1902 appendToASCIIBuffer(":/", 2);
1903 } else {
1904 copyURLPartsUntil(base, URLPart::PortEnd, c, nonUTF8QueryEncoding);
1905 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1906 copiedHost = true;
1907 }
1908 }
1909 if (!copiedHost) {
1910 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) + 1;
1911 appendToASCIIBuffer("//", 2);
1912 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1913 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1914 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1915 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1916 }
1917 }
1918 if (copyBaseWindowsDriveLetter(base)) {
1919 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1920 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 4;
1921 } else
1922 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + 1;
1923 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1924 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1925 break;
1926 case State::FileHost:
1927 LOG_FINAL_STATE("FileHost");
1928 if (takesTwoAdvancesUntilEnd(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c))
1929 && isWindowsDriveLetter(authorityOrHostBegin)) {
1930 syntaxViolation(authorityOrHostBegin);
1931 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1932 appendWindowsDriveLetter(authorityOrHostBegin);
1933 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = currentPosition(c);
1934 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1935 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1936 break;
1937 }
1938
1939 if (authorityOrHostBegin == c) {
1940 syntaxViolation(c);
1941 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1942 m_url.m_userStart = currentPosition(c) - 1;
1943 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1944 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1945 m_url.m_hostEnd = m_url.m_userStart;
1946 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1947 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_userStart + 1;
1948 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1949 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1950 break;
1951 }
1952
1953 if (!parseHostAndPort(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(authorityOrHostBegin, c))) {
1954 failure();
1955 return;
1956 }
1957
1958 syntaxViolation(c);
1959 if (isLocalhost(parsedDataView(m_url.m_passwordEnd, currentPosition(c) - m_url.m_passwordEnd))) {
1960 m_asciiBuffer.shrink(m_url.m_passwordEnd);
1961 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(c);
1962 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
1963 }
1964 appendToASCIIBuffer('/');
1965 m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash = m_url.m_hostEnd + m_url.m_portLength + 1;
1966 m_url.m_pathEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1967 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathAfterLastSlash;
1968 break;
1969 case State::PathStart:
1970 LOG_FINAL_STATE("PathStart");
1971 RELEASE_ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1972 case State::Path:
1973 LOG_FINAL_STATE("Path");
1974 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1975 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1976 break;
1977 case State::CannotBeABaseURLPath:
1978 LOG_FINAL_STATE("CannotBeABaseURLPath");
1979 m_url.m_pathEnd = currentPosition(c);
1980 m_url.m_queryEnd = m_url.m_pathEnd;
1981 break;
1982 case State::UTF8Query:
1983 LOG_FINAL_STATE("UTF8Query");
1984 ASSERT(queryBegin == CodePointIterator<CharacterType>());
1985 m_url.m_queryEnd = currentPosition(c);
1986 break;
1987 case State::NonUTF8Query:
1988 LOG_FINAL_STATE("NonUTF8Query");
1989 ASSERT(queryBegin != CodePointIterator<CharacterType>());
1990 encodeNonUTF8Query(queryBuffer, *nonUTF8QueryEncoding, CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(queryBegin, c));
1991 m_url.m_queryEnd = currentPosition(c);
1992 break;
1993 case State::Fragment:
1994 LOG_FINAL_STATE("Fragment");
1995 break;
1996 }
1997
1998 if (LIKELY(!m_didSeeSyntaxViolation)) {
1999 m_url.m_string = m_inputString;
2000 ASSERT(m_asciiBuffer.isEmpty());
2001 } else
2002 m_url.m_string = String::adopt(WTFMove(m_asciiBuffer));
2003 m_url.m_isValid = true;
2004 URL_PARSER_LOG("Parsed URL <%s>\n\n", m_url.m_string.utf8().data());
2005}
2006
2007template<typename CharacterType>
2008void URLParser::parseAuthority(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
2009{
2010 if (UNLIKELY(iterator.atEnd())) {
2011 syntaxViolation(iterator);
2012 m_url.m_userEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2013 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
2014 return;
2015 }
2016 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); advance(iterator)) {
2017 if (*iterator == ':') {
2018 m_url.m_userEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2019 auto iteratorAtColon = iterator;
2020 ++iterator;
2021 bool tabOrNewlineAfterColon = false;
2022 while (UNLIKELY(!iterator.atEnd() && isTabOrNewline(*iterator))) {
2023 tabOrNewlineAfterColon = true;
2024 ++iterator;
2025 }
2026 if (UNLIKELY(iterator.atEnd())) {
2027 syntaxViolation(iteratorAtColon);
2028 m_url.m_passwordEnd = m_url.m_userEnd;
2029 if (m_url.m_userEnd > m_url.m_userStart)
2030 appendToASCIIBuffer('@');
2031 return;
2032 }
2033 if (tabOrNewlineAfterColon)
2034 syntaxViolation(iteratorAtColon);
2035 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
2036 break;
2037 }
2038 utf8PercentEncode<WTF::isInUserInfoEncodeSet>(iterator);
2039 }
2040 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); advance(iterator))
2041 utf8PercentEncode<WTF::isInUserInfoEncodeSet>(iterator);
2042 m_url.m_passwordEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2043 if (!m_url.m_userEnd)
2044 m_url.m_userEnd = m_url.m_passwordEnd;
2045 appendToASCIIBuffer('@');
2046}

2048template<typename UnsignedIntegerType>
2049void URLParser::appendNumberToASCIIBuffer(UnsignedIntegerType number)
2050{
2051 LChar buf[sizeof(UnsignedIntegerType) * 3 + 1];
2052 LChar* end = std::end(buf);
2053 LChar* p = end;
2054 do {
2055 *--p = (number % 10) + '0';
2056 number /= 10;
2057 } while (number);
2058 appendToASCIIBuffer(p, end - p);
2059}

2061void URLParser::serializeIPv4(IPv4Address address)
2062{
2063 appendNumberToASCIIBuffer<uint8_t>(address >> 24);
2064 appendToASCIIBuffer('.');
2065 appendNumberToASCIIBuffer<uint8_t>(address >> 16);
2066 appendToASCIIBuffer('.');
2067 appendNumberToASCIIBuffer<uint8_t>(address >> 8);
2068 appendToASCIIBuffer('.');
2069 appendNumberToASCIIBuffer<uint8_t>(address);
2070}

2072static size_t zeroSequenceLength(const std::array<uint16_t, 8>& address, size_t begin)
2073{
2074 size_t end = begin;
2075 for (; end < 8; end++) {
2076 if (address[end])
2077 break;
2078 }
2079 return end - begin;
2080}
2081
2082static std::optional<size_t> findLongestZeroSequence(const std::array<uint16_t, 8>& address)
2083{
2084 std::optional<size_t> longest;
2085 size_t longestLength = 0;
2086 for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
2087 size_t length = zeroSequenceLength(address, i);
2088 if (length) {
2089 if (length > 1 && (!longest || longestLength < length)) {
2090 longest = i;
2091 longestLength = length;
2092 }
2093 i += length;
2094 }
2095 }
2096 return longest;
2097}

2099void URLParser::serializeIPv6Piece(uint16_t piece)
2100{
2101 bool printed = false;
2102 if (auto nibble0 = piece >> 12) {
2103 appendToASCIIBuffer(lowerNibbleToLowercaseASCIIHexDigit(nibble0));
2104 printed = true;
2105 }
2106 auto nibble1 = piece >> 8 & 0xF;
2107 if (printed || nibble1) {
2108 appendToASCIIBuffer(lowerNibbleToLowercaseASCIIHexDigit(nibble1));
2109 printed = true;
2110 }
2111 auto nibble2 = piece >> 4 & 0xF;
2112 if (printed || nibble2)
2113 appendToASCIIBuffer(lowerNibbleToLowercaseASCIIHexDigit(nibble2));
2114 appendToASCIIBuffer(lowerNibbleToLowercaseASCIIHexDigit(piece & 0xF));
2115}
2116
2117void URLParser::serializeIPv6(URLParser::IPv6Address address)
2118{
2119 appendToASCIIBuffer('[');
2120 auto compressPointer = findLongestZeroSequence(address);
2121 for (size_t piece = 0; piece < 8; piece++) {
2122 if (compressPointer && compressPointer.value() == piece) {
2123 ASSERT(!address[piece]);
2124 if (piece)
2125 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
2126 else
2127 appendToASCIIBuffer("::", 2);
2128 while (piece < 8 && !address[piece])
2129 piece++;
2130 if (piece == 8)
2131 break;
2132 }
2133 serializeIPv6Piece(address[piece]);
2134 if (piece < 7)
2135 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
2136 }
2137 appendToASCIIBuffer(']');
2138}

2140enum class URLParser::IPv4PieceParsingError {
2141 Failure,
2142 Overflow,
2143};
2144
2145template<typename CharacterType>
2146Expected<uint32_t, URLParser::IPv4PieceParsingError> URLParser::parseIPv4Piece(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator, bool& didSeeSyntaxViolation)
2147{
2148 enum class State : uint8_t {
2149 UnknownBase,
2150 Decimal,
2151 OctalOrHex,
2152 Octal,
2153 Hex,
2154 };
2155 State state = State::UnknownBase;
2156 CheckedUint32 value = 0;
2157 if (!iterator.atEnd() && *iterator == '.')
2158 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Failure);
2159 while (!iterator.atEnd()) {
2160 if (isTabOrNewline(*iterator)) {
2161 didSeeSyntaxViolation = true;
2162 ++iterator;
2163 continue;
2164 }
2165 if (*iterator == '.') {
2166 ASSERT(!value.hasOverflowed());
2167 return value.value();
2168 }
2169 switch (state) {
2170 case State::UnknownBase:
2171 if (UNLIKELY(*iterator == '0')) {
2172 ++iterator;
2173 state = State::OctalOrHex;
2174 break;
2175 }
2176 state = State::Decimal;
2177 break;
2178 case State::OctalOrHex:
2179 didSeeSyntaxViolation = true;
2180 if (*iterator == 'x' || *iterator == 'X') {
2181 ++iterator;
2182 state = State::Hex;
2183 break;
2184 }
2185 state = State::Octal;
2186 break;
2187 case State::Decimal:
2188 if (!isASCIIDigit(*iterator))
2189 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Failure);
2190 value *= 10;
2191 value += *iterator - '0';
2192 if (UNLIKELY(value.hasOverflowed()))
2193 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Overflow);
2194 ++iterator;
2195 break;
2196 case State::Octal:
2197 ASSERT(didSeeSyntaxViolation);
2198 if (*iterator < '0' || *iterator > '7')
2199 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Failure);
2200 value *= 8;
2201 value += *iterator - '0';
2202 if (UNLIKELY(value.hasOverflowed()))
2203 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Overflow);
2204 ++iterator;
2205 break;
2206 case State::Hex:
2207 ASSERT(didSeeSyntaxViolation);
2208 if (!isASCIIHexDigit(*iterator))
2209 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Failure);
2210 value *= 16;
2211 value += toASCIIHexValue(*iterator);
2212 if (UNLIKELY(value.hasOverflowed()))
2213 return makeUnexpected(IPv4PieceParsingError::Overflow);
2214 ++iterator;
2215 break;
2216 }
2217 }
2218 ASSERT(!value.hasOverflowed());
2219 return value.value();
2220}
2221
2222ALWAYS_INLINE static uint64_t pow256(size_t exponent)
2223{
2224 RELEASE_ASSERT(exponent <= 4);
2225 uint64_t values[5] = {1, 256, 256 * 256, 256 * 256 * 256, 256ull * 256 * 256 * 256 };
2226 return values[exponent];
2227}

2229enum class URLParser::IPv4ParsingError {
2230 Failure,
2231 NotIPv4,
2232};
2233
2234template<typename CharacterTypeForSyntaxViolation, typename CharacterType>
2235Expected<URLParser::IPv4Address, URLParser::IPv4ParsingError> URLParser::parseIPv4Host(const CodePointIterator<CharacterTypeForSyntaxViolation>& iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition, CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
2236{
2237 Vector<Expected<uint32_t, URLParser::IPv4PieceParsingError>, 4> items;
2238 bool didSeeSyntaxViolation = false;
2239 if (!iterator.atEnd() && *iterator == '.')
2240 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::NotIPv4);
2241 while (!iterator.atEnd()) {
2242 if (isTabOrNewline(*iterator)) {
2243 didSeeSyntaxViolation = true;
2244 ++iterator;
2245 continue;
2246 }
2247 if (items.size() >= 4)
2248 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::NotIPv4);
2249 items.append(parseIPv4Piece(iterator, didSeeSyntaxViolation));
2250 if (!iterator.atEnd() && *iterator == '.') {
2251 ++iterator;
2252 if (iterator.atEnd())
2253 didSeeSyntaxViolation = true;
2254 else if (*iterator == '.')
2255 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::NotIPv4);
2256 }
2257 }
2258 if (!iterator.atEnd() || !items.size() || items.size() > 4)
2259 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::NotIPv4);
2260 for (const auto& item : items) {
2261 if (!item.has_value() && item.error() == IPv4PieceParsingError::Failure)
2262 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::NotIPv4);
2263 }
2264 for (const auto& item : items) {
2265 if (!item.has_value() && item.error() == IPv4PieceParsingError::Overflow)
2266 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::Failure);
2267 }
2268 if (items.size() > 1) {
2269 for (size_t i = 0; i < items.size() - 1; i++) {
2270 if (items[i].value() > 255)
2271 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::Failure);
2272 }
2273 }
2274 if (items[items.size() - 1].value() >= pow256(5 - items.size()))
2275 return makeUnexpected(IPv4ParsingError::Failure);
2276
2277 if (didSeeSyntaxViolation)
2278 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2279 for (const auto& item : items) {
2280 if (item.value() > 255)
2281 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2282 }
2283
2284 if (UNLIKELY(items.size() != 4))
2285 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2286
2287 IPv4Address ipv4 = items.takeLast().value();
2288 for (size_t counter = 0; counter < items.size(); ++counter)
2289 ipv4 += items[counter].value() * pow256(3 - counter);
2290 return ipv4;
2291}

2293template<typename CharacterType>
2294std::optional<uint32_t> URLParser::parseIPv4PieceInsideIPv6(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
2295{
2296 if (iterator.atEnd())
2297 return std::nullopt;
2298 uint32_t piece = 0;
2299 bool leadingZeros = false;
2300 size_t digitCount = 0;
2301 while (!iterator.atEnd()) {
2302 if (!isASCIIDigit(*iterator))
2303 return std::nullopt;
2304 ++digitCount;
2305 if (!piece && *iterator == '0') {
2306 if (leadingZeros)
2307 return std::nullopt;
2308 leadingZeros = true;
2309 }
2310 if (!piece && *iterator == '0')
2311 leadingZeros = true;
2312 piece = piece * 10 + *iterator - '0';
2313 if (piece > 255)
2314 return std::nullopt;
2315 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
2316 if (iterator.atEnd())
2317 break;
2318 if (*iterator == '.')
2319 break;
2320 }
2321 if (piece && leadingZeros)
2322 return std::nullopt;
2323 return piece;
2324}

2326template<typename CharacterType>
2327std::optional<URLParser::IPv4Address> URLParser::parseIPv4AddressInsideIPv6(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
2328{
2329 IPv4Address address = 0;
2330 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
2331 if (std::optional<uint32_t> piece = parseIPv4PieceInsideIPv6(iterator))
2332 address = (address << 8) + piece.value();
2333 else
2334 return std::nullopt;
2335 if (i < 3) {
2336 if (iterator.atEnd())
2337 return std::nullopt;
2338 if (*iterator != '.')
2339 return std::nullopt;
2340 advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator);
2341 } else if (!iterator.atEnd())
2342 return std::nullopt;
2343 }
2344 ASSERT(iterator.atEnd());
2345 return address;
2346}

2348template<typename CharacterType>
2349std::optional<URLParser::IPv6Address> URLParser::parseIPv6Host(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> c)
2350{
2351 ASSERT(*c == '[');
2352 const auto hostBegin = c;
2353 advance(c, hostBegin);
2354 if (c.atEnd())
2355 return std::nullopt;
2356
2357 IPv6Address address = {{0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0}};
2358 size_t piecePointer = 0;
2359 std::optional<size_t> compressPointer;
2360 bool previousValueWasZero = false;
2361 bool immediatelyAfterCompress = false;
2362
2363 if (*c == ':') {
2364 advance(c, hostBegin);
2365 if (c.atEnd())
2366 return std::nullopt;
2367 if (*c != ':')
2368 return std::nullopt;
2369 advance(c, hostBegin);
2370 ++piecePointer;
2371 compressPointer = piecePointer;
2372 immediatelyAfterCompress = true;
2373 }
2374
2375 while (!c.atEnd()) {
2376 if (piecePointer == 8)
2377 return std::nullopt;
2378 if (*c == ':') {
2379 if (compressPointer)
2380 return std::nullopt;
2381 advance(c, hostBegin);
2382 ++piecePointer;
2383 compressPointer = piecePointer;
2384 immediatelyAfterCompress = true;
2385 if (previousValueWasZero)
2386 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2387 continue;
2388 }
2389 if (piecePointer == 6 || (compressPointer && piecePointer < 6)) {
2390 if (std::optional<IPv4Address> ipv4Address = parseIPv4AddressInsideIPv6(c)) {
2391 if (compressPointer && piecePointer == 5)
2392 return std::nullopt;
2393 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2394 address[piecePointer++] = ipv4Address.value() >> 16;
2395 address[piecePointer++] = ipv4Address.value() & 0xFFFF;
2396 c = { };
2397 break;
2398 }
2399 }
2400 uint16_t value = 0;
2401 size_t length = 0;
2402 bool leadingZeros = false;
2403 for (; length < 4; length++) {
2404 if (c.atEnd())
2405 break;
2406 if (!isASCIIHexDigit(*c))
2407 break;
2408 if (isASCIIUpper(*c))
2409 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2410 if (*c == '0' && !length)
2411 leadingZeros = true;
2412 value = value * 0x10 + toASCIIHexValue(*c);
2413 advance(c, hostBegin);
2414 }
2415
2416 previousValueWasZero = !value;
2417 if (UNLIKELY((value && leadingZeros) || (previousValueWasZero && (length > 1 || immediatelyAfterCompress))))
2418 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2419
2420 address[piecePointer++] = value;
2421 if (c.atEnd())
2422 break;
2423 if (piecePointer == 8 || *c != ':')
2424 return std::nullopt;
2425 advance(c, hostBegin);
2426 if (c.atEnd())
2427 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2428
2429 immediatelyAfterCompress = false;
2430 }
2431
2432 if (!c.atEnd())
2433 return std::nullopt;
2434
2435 if (compressPointer) {
2436 size_t swaps = piecePointer - compressPointer.value();
2437 piecePointer = 7;
2438 while (swaps)
2439 std::swap(address[piecePointer--], address[compressPointer.value() + swaps-- - 1]);
2440 } else if (piecePointer != 8)
2441 return std::nullopt;
2442
2443 std::optional<size_t> possibleCompressPointer = findLongestZeroSequence(address);
2444 if (possibleCompressPointer)
2445 possibleCompressPointer.value()++;
2446 if (UNLIKELY(compressPointer != possibleCompressPointer))
2447 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2448
2449 return address;
2450}

2452template<typename CharacterType>
2453URLParser::LCharBuffer URLParser::percentDecode(const LChar* input, size_t length, const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition)
2454{
2455 LCharBuffer output;
2456 output.reserveInitialCapacity(length);
2457
2458 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
2459 uint8_t byte = input[i];
2460 if (byte != '%')
2461 output.uncheckedAppend(byte);
2462 else if (length > 2 && i < length - 2) {
2463 if (isASCIIHexDigit(input[i + 1]) && isASCIIHexDigit(input[i + 2])) {
2464 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2465 output.uncheckedAppend(toASCIIHexValue(input[i + 1], input[i + 2]));
2466 i += 2;
2467 } else
2468 output.uncheckedAppend(byte);
2469 } else
2470 output.uncheckedAppend(byte);
2471 }
2472 return output;
2473}

2516template<typename CharacterType> std::optional<URLParser::LCharBuffer> URLParser::domainToASCII(StringImpl& domain, const CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition)

2520 size_t length = domain.length();
2521 if (domain.is8Bit()) {
2522 const LChar* characters = domain.characters8();
2523 ascii.reserveInitialCapacity(length);
2524 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
2525 if (UNLIKELY(isASCIIUpper(characters[i])))
2526 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2527 ascii.uncheckedAppend(toASCIILower(characters[i]));
2528 }
2529 } else {
2530 const UChar* characters = domain.characters16();
2531 ascii.reserveInitialCapacity(length);
2532 for (size_t i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
2533 if (UNLIKELY(isASCIIUpper(characters[i])))
2534 syntaxViolation(iteratorForSyntaxViolationPosition);
2535 ascii.uncheckedAppend(toASCIILower(characters[i]));
2536 }
2537 }
2538 return ascii;
2539 }
2540
2541 UChar hostnameBuffer[hostnameBufferLength];
2542 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
2543 UIDNAInfo processingDetails = UIDNA_INFO_INITIALIZER;
2544 int32_t numCharactersConverted = uidna_nameToASCII(&internationalDomainNameTranscoder(), StringView(domain).upconvertedCharacters(), domain.length(), hostnameBuffer, hostnameBufferLength, &processingDetails, &error);
2545
2546 if (U_SUCCESS(error) && !(processingDetails.errors & ~allowedNameToASCIIErrors) && numCharactersConverted) {

2550 ASSERT(!isASCIIUpper(hostnameBuffer[i]));

2554#endif // ASSERT_ENABLED

2572template<typename CharacterType>
2573bool URLParser::parsePort(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>& iterator)
2574{
2575 if (UNLIKELY(m_urlIsFile))
2576 return false;
2577
2578 ASSERT(*iterator == ':');
2579 auto colonIterator = iterator;
2580 advance(iterator, colonIterator);
2581 uint32_t port = 0;
2582 if (UNLIKELY(iterator.atEnd())) {
2583 unsigned portLength = currentPosition(colonIterator) - m_url.m_hostEnd;
2584 RELEASE_ASSERT(portLength <= URL::maxPortLength);
2585 m_url.m_portLength = portLength;
2586 syntaxViolation(colonIterator);
2587 return true;
2588 }
2589 size_t digitCount = 0;
2590 bool leadingZeros = false;
2591 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); ++iterator) {
2592 if (UNLIKELY(isTabOrNewline(*iterator))) {
2593 syntaxViolation(colonIterator);
2594 continue;
2595 }
2596 if (isASCIIDigit(*iterator)) {
2597 if (*iterator == '0' && !digitCount)
2598 leadingZeros = true;
2599 ++digitCount;
2600 port = port * 10 + *iterator - '0';
2601 if (port > std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max())
2602 return false;
2603 } else
2604 return false;
2605 }
2606
2607 if (port && leadingZeros)
2608 syntaxViolation(colonIterator);
2609
2610 if (!port && digitCount > 1)
2611 syntaxViolation(colonIterator);
2612
2613 ASSERT(port == static_cast<uint16_t>(port));
2614 if (UNLIKELY(defaultPortForProtocol(parsedDataView(0, m_url.m_schemeEnd)) == static_cast<uint16_t>(port)))
2615 syntaxViolation(colonIterator);
2616 else {
2617 appendToASCIIBuffer(':');
2618 ASSERT(port <= std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max());
2619 appendNumberToASCIIBuffer<uint16_t>(static_cast<uint16_t>(port));
2620 }
2621
2622 unsigned portLength = currentPosition(iterator) - m_url.m_hostEnd;
2623 RELEASE_ASSERT(portLength <= URL::maxPortLength);
2624 m_url.m_portLength = portLength;
2625 return true;
2626}
2627
2628template<typename CharacterType>
2629bool URLParser::subdomainStartsWithXNDashDash(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
2630{
2631 enum class State : uint8_t {
2632 NotAtSubdomainBeginOrInXNDashDash,
2633 AtSubdomainBegin,
2634 AfterX,
2635 AfterN,
2636 AfterFirstDash,
2637 } state { State::AtSubdomainBegin };
2638
2639 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); advance<CharacterType, ReportSyntaxViolation::No>(iterator)) {
2640 CharacterType c = *iterator;
2641
2642 // These characters indicate the end of the host.
2643 if (c == ':' || c == '/' || c == '?' || c == '#')
2644 return false;
2645
2646 switch (state) {
2647 case State::NotAtSubdomainBeginOrInXNDashDash:
2648 break;
2649 case State::AtSubdomainBegin:
2650 if (c == 'x' || c == 'X') {
2651 state = State::AfterX;
2652 continue;
2653 }
2654 break;
2655 case State::AfterX:
2656 if (c == 'n' || c == 'N') {
2657 state = State::AfterN;
2658 continue;
2659 }
2660 break;
2661 case State::AfterN:
2662 if (c == '-') {
2663 state = State::AfterFirstDash;
2664 continue;
2665 }
2666 break;
2667 case State::AfterFirstDash:
2668 if (c == '-')
2669 return true;
2670 break;
2671 }
2672
2673 if (c == '.')
2674 state = State::AtSubdomainBegin;
2675 else
2676 state = State::NotAtSubdomainBeginOrInXNDashDash;
2677 }
2678 return false;
2679}
2680
2681bool URLParser::subdomainStartsWithXNDashDash(StringImpl& host)
2682{
2683 if (host.is8Bit()) {
2684 const LChar* begin = host.characters8();
2685 return subdomainStartsWithXNDashDash(CodePointIterator<LChar>(begin, begin + host.length()));
2686 }
2687 const UChar* begin = host.characters16();
2688 return subdomainStartsWithXNDashDash(CodePointIterator<UChar>(begin, begin + host.length()));
2689}

2691template<typename CharacterType>
2692bool URLParser::parseHostAndPort(CodePointIterator<CharacterType> iterator)
2693{
2694 if (iterator.atEnd())
2695 return false;
2696 if (*iterator == ':')
2697 return false;
2698 if (*iterator == '[') {
2699 auto ipv6End = iterator;
2700 while (!ipv6End.atEnd() && *ipv6End != ']')
2701 ++ipv6End;
2702 if (ipv6End.atEnd())
2703 return false;
2704 if (auto address = parseIPv6Host(CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(iterator, ipv6End))) {
2705 serializeIPv6(address.value());
2706 if (!ipv6End.atEnd()) {
2707 advance(ipv6End);
2708 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(ipv6End);
2709 if (!ipv6End.atEnd() && *ipv6End == ':')
2710 return parsePort(ipv6End);
2711 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
2712 return ipv6End.atEnd();
2713 }
2714 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(ipv6End);
2715 return true;
2716 }
2717 return false;
2718 }
2719
2720 if (!m_urlIsSpecial) {
2721 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); ++iterator) {
2722 if (UNLIKELY(isTabOrNewline(*iterator))) {
2723 syntaxViolation(iterator);
2724 continue;
2725 }
2726 if (*iterator == ':')
2727 break;
2728 if (UNLIKELY(isForbiddenHostCodePoint(*iterator) && *iterator != '%'))
2729 return false;
2730 utf8PercentEncode<isInSimpleEncodeSet>(iterator);
2731 }
2732 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2733 if (iterator.atEnd()) {
2734 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
2735 return true;
2736 }
2737 return parsePort(iterator);
2738 }
2739
2740 if (LIKELY(!m_hostHasPercentOrNonASCII && !subdomainStartsWithXNDashDash(iterator))) {
2741 auto hostIterator = iterator;
2742 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); ++iterator) {
2743 if (isTabOrNewline(*iterator))
2744 continue;
2745 if (*iterator == ':')
2746 break;
2747 if (isForbiddenHostCodePoint(*iterator))
2748 return false;
2749 }
2750 auto address = parseIPv4Host(hostIterator, CodePointIterator<CharacterType>(hostIterator, iterator));
2751 if (address) {
2752 serializeIPv4(address.value());
2753 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2754 if (iterator.atEnd()) {
2755 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
2756 return true;
2757 }
2758 return parsePort(iterator);
2759 }
2760 if (address.error() == IPv4ParsingError::Failure)
2761 return false;
2762 for (; hostIterator != iterator; ++hostIterator) {
2763 if (UNLIKELY(isTabOrNewline(*hostIterator))) {
2764 syntaxViolation(hostIterator);
2765 continue;
2766 }
2767 if (UNLIKELY(isASCIIUpper(*hostIterator)))
2768 syntaxViolation(hostIterator);
2769 appendToASCIIBuffer(toASCIILower(*hostIterator));
2770 }
2771 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2772 if (!hostIterator.atEnd())
2773 return parsePort(hostIterator);
2774 unsigned portLength = currentPosition(iterator) - m_url.m_hostEnd;
2775 RELEASE_ASSERT(portLength <= URL::maxPortLength);
2776 m_url.m_portLength = portLength;
2777 return true;
2778 }
2779
2780 const auto hostBegin = iterator;
2781
2782 LCharBuffer utf8Encoded;
2783 for (; !iterator.atEnd(); ++iterator) {
2784 if (UNLIKELY(isTabOrNewline(*iterator))) {
2785 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2786 continue;
2787 }
2788 if (*iterator == ':')
2789 break;
2790 if (UNLIKELY(!isASCII(*iterator)))
2791 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2792
2793 uint8_t buffer[U8_MAX_LENGTH];
2794 int32_t offset = 0;
2795 UBool isError = false;
2796 U8_APPEND(buffer, offset, U8_MAX_LENGTH, *iterator, isError);
2797 if (isError)
2798 return false;
2799 utf8Encoded.append(buffer, offset);
2800 }
2801 LCharBuffer percentDecoded = percentDecode(utf8Encoded.data(), utf8Encoded.size(), hostBegin);
2802 String domain = String::fromUTF8(percentDecoded.data(), percentDecoded.size());
2803 if (domain.isNull())
2804 return false;
2805 if (domain != StringView(percentDecoded.data(), percentDecoded.size()))
2806 syntaxViolation(hostBegin);
2807 auto asciiDomain = domainToASCII(*domain.impl(), hostBegin);
2808 if (!asciiDomain || hasForbiddenHostCodePoint(asciiDomain.value()))
2809 return false;
2810 LCharBuffer& asciiDomainValue = asciiDomain.value();
2811 const LChar* asciiDomainCharacters = asciiDomainValue.data();
2812
2813 auto address = parseIPv4Host(hostBegin, CodePointIterator<LChar>(asciiDomainValue.begin(), asciiDomainValue.end()));
2814 if (address) {
2815 serializeIPv4(address.value());
2816 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2817 if (iterator.atEnd()) {
2818 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
2819 return true;
2820 }
2821 return parsePort(iterator);
2822 }
2823 if (address.error() == IPv4ParsingError::Failure)
2824 return false;
2825
2826 appendToASCIIBuffer(asciiDomainCharacters, asciiDomainValue.size());
2827 m_url.m_hostEnd = currentPosition(iterator);
2828 if (!iterator.atEnd())
2829 return parsePort(iterator);
2830 m_url.m_portLength = 0;
2831 return true;
2832}

2834std::optional<String> URLParser::formURLDecode(StringView input)
2835{
2836 auto utf8 = input.utf8(StrictConversion);
2837 if (utf8.isNull())
2838 return std::nullopt;
2839 auto percentDecoded = percentDecode(utf8.dataAsUInt8Ptr(), utf8.length());
2840 return String::fromUTF8ReplacingInvalidSequences(percentDecoded.data(), percentDecoded.size());
2841}

2843// https://url.spec.whatwg.org/#concept-urlencoded-parser
2844auto URLParser::parseURLEncodedForm(StringView input) -> URLEncodedForm
2845{
2846 URLEncodedForm output;
2847 for (StringView bytes : input.split('&')) {
2848 auto equalIndex = bytes.find('=');
2849 if (equalIndex == notFound) {
2850 auto name = formURLDecode(bytes.toString().replace('+', 0x20));
2851 if (name)
2852 output.append({ name.value(), emptyString() });
2853 } else {
2854 auto name = formURLDecode(bytes.substring(0, equalIndex).toString().replace('+', 0x20));
2855 auto value = formURLDecode(bytes.substring(equalIndex + 1).toString().replace('+', 0x20));
2856 if (name && value)
2857 output.append({ name.value(), value.value() });
2858 }
2859 }
2860 return output;
2861}
2862
2863static void serializeURLEncodedForm(const String& input, Vector<LChar>& output)
2864{
2865 auto utf8 = input.utf8(StrictConversion);
2866 const char* data = utf8.data();
2867 for (size_t i = 0; i < utf8.length(); ++i) {
2868 const char byte = data[i];
2869 if (byte == 0x20)
2870 output.append(0x2B);
2871 else if (byte == 0x2A
2872 || byte == 0x2D
2873 || byte == 0x2E
2874 || (byte >= 0x30 && byte <= 0x39)
2875 || (byte >= 0x41 && byte <= 0x5A)
2876 || byte == 0x5F
2877 || (byte >= 0x61 && byte <= 0x7A)) // FIXME: Put these in the characterClassTable to avoid branches.
2878 output.append(byte);
2879 else
2880 percentEncodeByte(byte, output);
2881 }
2882}
2883
2884String URLParser::serialize(const URLEncodedForm& tuples)
2885{
2886 if (tuples.isEmpty())
2887 return { };
2888
2889 Vector<LChar> output;
2890 for (auto& tuple : tuples) {
2891 if (!output.isEmpty())
2892 output.append('&');
2893 serializeURLEncodedForm(tuple.key, output);
2894 output.append('=');
2895 serializeURLEncodedForm(tuple.value, output);
2896 }
2897 return String::adopt(WTFMove(output));
2898}

2900const UIDNA& URLParser::internationalDomainNameTranscoder()
2901{
2902 static UIDNA* encoder;
2903 static std::once_flag onceFlag;
2904 std::call_once(onceFlag, [] {
2905 UErrorCode error = U_ZERO_ERROR;
2906 encoder = uidna_openUTS46(UIDNA_CHECK_BIDI | UIDNA_CHECK_CONTEXTJ | UIDNA_NONTRANSITIONAL_TO_UNICODE | UIDNA_NONTRANSITIONAL_TO_ASCII, &error);
2907 if (UNLIKELY(U_FAILURE(error)))
2908 CRASH_WITH_INFO(error);
2909 RELEASE_ASSERT(encoder);
2910 });
2911 return *encoder;
2912}

2914bool URLParser::allValuesEqual(const URL& a, const URL& b)
2915{
2916 URL_PARSER_LOG("%d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %s\n%d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d %s",
2917 a.m_isValid,
2918 a.m_cannotBeABaseURL,
2919 a.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily,
2920 a.m_schemeEnd,
2921 a.m_userStart,
2922 a.m_userEnd,
2923 a.m_passwordEnd,
2924 a.m_hostEnd,
2925 a.m_hostEnd + a.m_portLength,
2926 a.m_pathAfterLastSlash,
2927 a.m_pathEnd,
2928 a.m_queryEnd,
2929 a.m_string.utf8().data(),
2930 b.m_isValid,
2931 b.m_cannotBeABaseURL,
2932 b.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily,
2933 b.m_schemeEnd,
2934 b.m_userStart,
2935 b.m_userEnd,
2936 b.m_passwordEnd,
2937 b.m_hostEnd,
2938 b.m_hostEnd + b.m_portLength,
2939 b.m_pathAfterLastSlash,
2940 b.m_pathEnd,
2941 b.m_queryEnd,
2942 b.m_string.utf8().data());
2943
2944 return a.m_string == b.m_string
2945 && a.m_isValid == b.m_isValid
2946 && a.m_cannotBeABaseURL == b.m_cannotBeABaseURL
2947 && a.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily == b.m_protocolIsInHTTPFamily
2948 && a.m_schemeEnd == b.m_schemeEnd
2949 && a.m_userStart == b.m_userStart
2950 && a.m_userEnd == b.m_userEnd
2951 && a.m_passwordEnd == b.m_passwordEnd
2952 && a.m_hostEnd == b.m_hostEnd
2953 && a.m_portLength == b.m_portLength
2954 && a.m_pathAfterLastSlash == b.m_pathAfterLastSlash
2955 && a.m_pathEnd == b.m_pathEnd
2956 && a.m_queryEnd == b.m_queryEnd;
2957}

2959bool URLParser::internalValuesConsistent(const URL& url)
2960{
2961 return url.m_schemeEnd <= url.m_userStart
2962 && url.m_userStart <= url.m_userEnd
2963 && url.m_userEnd <= url.m_passwordEnd
2964 && url.m_passwordEnd <= url.m_hostEnd
2965 && url.m_hostEnd + url.m_portLength <= url.m_pathAfterLastSlash
2966 && url.m_pathAfterLastSlash <= url.m_pathEnd
2967 && url.m_pathEnd <= url.m_queryEnd
2968 && url.m_queryEnd <= url.m_string.length();
2969}
